tip.text: Something different with Aperitif tasting instead of wine.
Pork shoulder is amazing. Chicken and biscuit is a huge portion and the shrimp and grits is a classic
Langos and dan Dan noodles are amazing. You won't be disappointed
The food here is amazing. The portion is very big and seafood is fresh. The small mussels starter would be considered large in most places. Even the veggies are amazing.
Go for a guided tour in the afternoon. You may get lucky and get to see the stage from the back.
While they don't have many English guides, it's worth it to wait for one and get a tour. There's so much history and stories. If an English guide is giving a tour, feel free to ask to join.
Amazing view. Hot water doesn't always work but the experience is positive.
